      "writtenOn": "2018-08-15T03:00:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, sounds good.\n\nJust to check: for row length, the case I was thinking of was that, if we decompressed to a 4x4 rgba texture, and the row length was 8 pixels, and we unpacked to a tightly packed sequence of 4x4x4bpp \u003d 64 bytes, wouldn\u0027t glTexImage2D expect the third row to occur at 8 px * 4bpp * 2 rows \u003d byte 64 and the fourth row to occur at 8 px * 4bpp * 3 rows \u003d byte 96 which might read out of bounds? Though, it\u0027s late / I\u0027m tired so I might be getting something completely backwards here",
      "parentUuid": "ea4e8d7e_2f059b6c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 715,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 716,
        "endChar": 70
